title: Nerve agent found on face of assassinated half-brother of North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un, police say - 9news.com.au
text:
Nerve agent found on face of assassinated half-brother of North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un, police say By 9NEWS 
Police in Malaysia say the half brother of North Korea's leader who was killed in a Kuala Lumpur airport more than a week ago had a nerve agent on his eye and his face. 
A statement Friday from the inspector general of police said that a preliminary analysis from the Chemistry Department of Malaysia identified the agent as "VX NERVE AGENT." Kim Jong Nam was killed at a Malaysian airport on February 13. North Korea leader Kim Jong Un. 
Kim Jong Nam, the half brother of North Korean leader Kim Jong Un, died Feb. 13 shortly after two women put a substance on his face while he was checking in for a flight. Â© Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
